# Principle Pack — Generic Engineering

> Industry-neutral best-practice norms used as one of three sources
> for `/hx-constitution` synthesis. Tag each principle with
> `[enforceable: arch-test|lint]` if a deterministic guardrail can
> check it; otherwise tag `[inferential]` so `/hx-review` covers it.
>
> Add tech-specific packs (e.g. `python.md`, `react.md`, `spring.md`)
> alongside this file. Team-extensible.

> Provenance (T15)
> - Authoritative paradigm: Google Engineering Practices + Alibaba Java Development Manual + Thoughtworks engineering values — industry-neutral baseline principles
> - Investigation protocol: each principle is industry-neutral and tagged `[enforceable: arch-test|lint]` when a deterministic guardrail can check it; otherwise `[inferential]` so `/hx-review` covers it; domain-specific tightening lives in sibling packs (`python.md`, `spring.md`, `react.md`, …)
> - Output form: compact numbered cards `P-G-N` — **Rule** (imperative) · **Why** (what breaks) · enforceability tag; consumed by `/hx-constitution` and merged with observed project patterns to synthesize the project constitution

---

## P-G-1 Tests verify behavior, not implementation details

- Rule: a test fails only when the user-visible behavior or contract changes.
- Why: tests coupled to internals decay fast and lock in bad designs.
- [inferential]

## P-G-2 No silent failures

- Rule: every error path is either handled, logged, or re-raised with context.
- Why: silent failures convert outages into mysteries.
- [enforceable: lint]

## P-G-3 Pure functions for business rules

- Rule: business logic functions have no I/O; I/O is at the edges.
- Why: testability, reasoning, and reuse.
- [inferential]

## P-G-4 Reversible decisions preferred

- Rule: choose the option easier to undo when trade-offs are close.
- Why: irreversible lock-in is the most expensive mistake category.
- [inferential]

## P-G-5 Single source of truth for any fact

- Rule: any project fact (version, threshold, contract) lives in exactly one place.
- Why: duplication drifts; drift breaks at the worst time.
- [inferential]

## P-G-6 Public APIs are documented at their definition site

- Rule: exported functions / types / endpoints carry a one-paragraph doc.
- Why: callers cannot read the implementation; the signature is the contract.
- [enforceable: lint]

## P-G-7 Logs carry structured context

- Rule: include request_id (or equivalent correlation key) on every log line.
- Why: post-mortem speed is bounded by log searchability.
- [enforceable: lint]
